<doc id="229444" wikidata="Q350543" url="?curid=229444" title="Birkenau (disambiguation)">
<text>[[Auschwitz II-Birkenau]] was a Nazi-German extermination camp, near Brzezinka, Poland, within the Auschwitz concentration camp complex during World War II.

Birkenau may also refer to:
* Birkenau (Odenwald), a municipality in the Odenwald in southern Hesse in Germany
* Brzezinka or Birkenau, a Polish village
* &quot;Birkenau&quot; (painting), a cycle of four paintings by Gerhard Richter

